post_text:
Dear Delaney and Roderick Families,

The Commissioner of Elementary and Secondary Education Jeff Riley cancelled MCAS for this school year. He sent the following notice to superintendents on Friday evening:
"MCAS Update: We previously requested and received a waiver from the federal requirement for annual statewide student assessment. Now, with the state legislation enacted, the MCAS testing requirement is waived for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year.

As a result of these federal and state actions and in light of the on-going health crisis, I am cancelling this spring’s regular administration of grade-level MCAS tests for students in grades 3-10."

Please let me know if you have any questions. Have a great weekend!

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools

post_text:
Dear Delaney and Roderick Families,

I am very sorry for the late notice, but out of an abundance of caution I am closing Delaney and Roderick Schools tomorrow, Friday, March 13, 2020. Nothing in Wrentham has changed since my email from earlier today. However, I understand the concerns about coronavirus in our community and think it best to close school. I will participate in a conference call with the Department of Elementary and Secondary Education tomorrow morning. After that, I will make longer terms plans for the district in collaboration with the King Philip Regional School District. I will email you tomorrow with the details.

Again, I apologize for the late notice. Have a nice evening. I will be in touch tomorrow.

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools

post_text:
Hi Wrentham Families,

If you're looking for a productive way to pass time over this break, check out our Caught Coding Challenge! Your challenge is to catch your student coding at home. If your student completes an Hour of Coding at home, fill out the “Hour of Code - Caught Coding” form in the WPS App for your student to be entered to win an extra technology class exploring with robots for their entire class! You can find the form on the home screen of the app by tapping "Caught Coding" or by:
- Opening the App
- Tapping "More"
- Tapping "Hour of Coding - Caught Coding"

If you don't have the app you can search Wrentham Public Schools in the Android or Apple App Stores and look for the Wildcat logo. The student's name will also be added to our Hour of Code headline page! One entry per student. All entry forms are due by Friday, January 3rd. A winner from each grade will be randomly selected on Monday, January 5th.

Some links to coding resources are in the comments:

Dear WPS Community,

Good evening! I am writing to tell you about the weather forecast for our area. Wrentham will be under a winter weather advisory from 1:00 a.m. through 1:00 p.m. on Tuesday, 12/17/2019. We are supposed to get 2-4 inches of snow followed by sleet and freezing rain. The timing of the storm makes it difficult to know whether we will have school. I will talk with the Wrentham DPW, our Facilities Manager, and the KP superintendent tomorrow morning before I make the decision. I will call you by 5:30 a.m. if school is delayed or closed.

Have a nice night!

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools

post_text:
Dear WPS Community,

I just completed the after-action review meeting regarding our delay this morning due to the power outage. We identified many things that went well and areas for improvement in case we experience a similar situation in the future. I want to share three points about today that will bring closure to the day:

-The schools did not lose power when the accident occurred at 5:15 am. National Grid shut the power off when they arrived to fix the problem, around 7:10 am. That is why the delay notice went out so late.
-The YMCA, Wrentham PD, and Delaney and Roderick staff members were amazing! They remained positive, responsive, and supportive throughout the morning.
- Most importantly, the driver of the vehicle that hit the pole was not injured.

Thank you again for your patience today. Let's hope tomorrow morning is better!

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools

post_text:
Good Morning,

Earlier this morning, Bus 7 had a minor accident involving a parked car at approximately 8:05 a.m. The bus tire connected with the bumper of a parked car. This caused a brief delay in traveling to school as the police arrived on scene following protocol. There were no injuries and Bus 7 families were alerted as soon as we were contacted by the bus company.

All arrived safely at school shortly after 8:30 a.m. and were greeted by Miss Maloney, Mr. Martes, and Mr. Worth. Students were happy and smiling as they walked to class and the day continued as planned.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to call.

Sincerely,

Vanessa

Vanessa Beauchaine, Ed.D.
Director of Curriculum, Instruction, and Assessment

Open House/Curriculum Night
Open House/Curriculum Night is when students’ teachers share an overview of the school year with students’ parents and guardians. Teachers will discuss what the students will learn, classroom procedures, field trips, and other important information. The date for the Delaney School Open House/Curriculum Night is Wednesday, September 18. The Roderick School Open House/Curriculum Night is Thursday, September 19. Principals Martes and Maloney will email you with additional details as we get closer to the dates.

post_text:
Dear WPS Community,

Last week, the Sun Chronicle ran an article about the start of school in Wrentham. Unfortunately, they printed the wrong date for the first day of school. They printed a correction, but I want to make certain everyone knows when school starts for Delaney and Roderick students.

The first day of school for Delaney and Roderick students, kindergarten through grade 6, is Tuesday, September 3rd. This is the day after Labor Day.

I apologize for the confusion. Please let me know if you have any questions.

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools
camerona@wrenthamschools.org

Early Release Dismissal Time Changed to 11:30
We are changing the dismissal time on early release days from 12:00 to 11:30 (dismissal time on regular days will remain 2:45). We made the change to benefit students. The 12:00 dismissal time resulted in a very long day with no lunch, particularly for our students with long bus rides home. For 2019-2020, the early release days are:
Thursday, September 26, Professional Development
Wednesday, November 27, Thanksgiving
Wednesday, December 4, Parent/Teacher Conferences
Thursday, December 5, Parent/Teacher Conferences
Friday, January 17, Professional Development
Tuesday, February 4, Professional Development
Wednesday, March 25, Parent/Teacher Conferences
Thursday, March 26, Parent/Teacher Conferences
Friday, May 22, Professional Development
Wednesday, June 17, Last Day of School

post_text:
No More Bus Fees!!!
We were able to eliminate bus fees for the 2019-2020 school year! No families will pay for their children to ride the bus to Delaney or Roderick Schools. Thank you to the School Committee, Town Administrator, Board of Selectmen, Finance Committee, and voters at the Annual Spring Town Meeting for supporting a budget that allowed us to eliminate this fee.

post_text:
New School Visitor Procedure
We are excited to introduce a new school security initiative. Starting this school year, we are requiring every adult who visits during school hours to present their driver’s license to office staff members. The license will be scanned by our new visitor screening system, called Raptor. The system will vet and document every visitor and print a visitor badge. Please remember to bring your driver’s license when you visit the schools during the school day.

post_text:
Dear WPS Families,

The National Weather Service issued a severe weather warning for Norfolk County. They are predicting snow starting tomorrow afternoon around 2:00, transitioning to sleet and freezing rain overnight and finishing as rain around sunrise on Wednesday morning. Based on the timeline in that forecast, Delaney and Roderick will be open regular hours tomorrow, Tuesday, February 12. Depending on how the storm develops, I may cancel after-school activities. If that happens, or in the unlikely event that we have to close school early, I will send you an email tomorrow morning.

Thank you for your patience as I navigate the best path forward for our students. Please let me know if you have any questions. Have a great night!

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools

camerona@wrenthamschools.org

February 8, 2019 at 12:30 PM ·

Tonight’s the night!! Some answers to some questions we’ve received:

1. Do I have to lip sync? (NO. The lip sync battle teams have been hard at work so they can perform for you tonight! You *will* have the opportunity to karaoke if you wish! Or, you can stick to dancing)

2. The event is at a country club. Do I have to dress up? (NO. There is no dress code!)

3. Will there be food? (YES. We will have passed apps for you to enjoy.)

4. What else will we be doing? (RAFFLES! SILENT AUCTIONS!! Our team has been hard at work and have many raffle and silent auction items for you to bid on. Raffle tickets will be sold at the door. PayPal will be accepted!)

5. Can I still get tickets? (YES. A limited number of tickets will also be sold at the door)

Did we miss something? Ask in the comments and we’ll get right back to you! See you tonight!! 🎤

The snow, rain, frigid temperatures, and wild chill have made many Wrentham side streets and the Delaney and Roderick parking lots and sidewalks treacherously icy. Therefore, Delaney and Roderick Schools will be closed tomorrow, Tuesday, January 22. Please stay safe if you go outside.

Yours truly,

Allan Cameron, Superintendent of Wrentham Public Schools

post_text: We are so grateful for the support WEST - Wrentham Elementary Schools Trust gives to innovative learning experiences for our students!!!
shared_text:
WEST - Wrentham Elementary Schools Trust
January 18, 2019 at 12:56 PM ·

Something special happened in the Roderick Library last night. WEST set a new Grant Night record by funding $33,000 in exciting and innovative grants for Delaney and Roderick elementary students! Thanks to the teachers for their creative ideas for inspiring a love of learning in Wrentham's kids. And thanks to you for supporting WEST and making this all possible!

post_text: Don't forget to include the Digital Citizenship Night on this Thursday, October 25th at 7:00pm on your schedule for this week. One of the topics we'll discuss is screen time. Can there be too much? How can using a device for extended periods of time impact a child? Should we have a family plan for device usage? Childcare will be provided.

post_text: SAVE THE DATE for our Digital Citizenship Parent Night! Thursday, October 25th at 7:00pm in the Vogel Auditorium. Come and engage with the WPS Technology Teachers and Director of Technology on issues such as the impact of screen time and social media on our developing students. There will be presentations followed by a time of discussion and Q&A. Childcare will be provided in the Delaney Cafeteria. Looking forward to seeing you there!

post_text:
We hope that you have had a wonderful summer! The staff is working hard to prepare the schools for the start of another year. 8/27/18 will be the Meet & Greet. Delaney School's will be from 9:45-10:30. Roderick School's will be from 10:45-11:30.
Also on 8/27/18 will be a PTO Sponsored Meet & Greet Picnic from 10:00-12:00 in the Delaney Bus Circle. Bring a blanket and some lunch. The Kona Shaved Ice Truck will be back!! Opening Day will be 8/28/18, which is a full day for Grades 1-6 with Orientation for PreK & Kindergarten. Please direct any questions to the Delaney or Roderick Offices.
